FT  16 JUN 92 / UK Company News: Clarke Hooper US disposal
Clarke Hooper has sold a US business for Dollars 462,500 (Pounds 254,000),
the proceeds of which will be used for local capital requirements and to
reduce group indebted-ness.
The disposal is the Los Angeles based business of its US subsidiary, Joseph
Potocki &amp; Associates. JP&amp;A broke even in the year ended April 30 1991 and
incurred estimated pre-tax losses of Dollars 273,000 in 1991-92, including
losses of the Atlanta office which was closed in April.
Mr Alan Penson, group chief executive, said the sale represented further
progress consistent with the restructuringto strengthen the core business
with selective US divestment.
